message:
Dear JS developers, I have  a question. What debugging files do you use? I had a situation where this was part of my code and Chrome didn't tell about the syntax error:

// No semi-colon after "file_data"
var file_data
file_data = $(item).prop('files')[0];

I switched to Firefox and it gave a hint about the missing semi-colon, but I wanna hear more about how do you usually verify your code?

Thanks
